article.headline: N. Arizona 88, Montana 81
article.story: MISSOULA, Mont. (AP) -- Kyle Landry and Ruben Boykin Jr. combined for 38 points and 22 rebounds in leading Northern Arizona to an 88-81 win over Montana Thursday night. Landry scored 16 of his 20 points in the first half when the Lumberjacks (15-11, 9-5 Big Sky) raced to a 51-38 lead. Tyrone Bazy scored 14 of his 16 points after intermission. His driving left-handed layup with 56 seconds to play put the Jacks up 83-78 and thwarted a Montana second-half rally. Bazy made 3-of-4 free throws down the stretch to seal the win. Boykin finished with 18 points, 11 rebounds and five assists while Josh Wilson added 11 points and five assists for NAU, which is now in second place in the league standings. Cameron Rundles scored 23 points and dished out five assists to pace Montana (14-14, 8-6), which trailed by as many as 16 points in the first half. The Griz climbed to 56-55 on a 3-pointer by Jordan Hasquet with 14:14 to play, but Stephen Sir responded with a 3-pointer to give the Jacks breathing room. Montana again closed to 76-73 with 4:00 to play on a pair of free throws by Andrew Strait, but missed an opportunity to get closer when Strait missed two free throws with 3:24 to play. Hasquet added 16 points and seven rebounds while Strait had 12 points and nine rebounds for the Griz.
